import os
import folium
import requests
import pandas
import json

arrest_table = pandas.read_csv("http://www.hcbravo.org/IntroDataSci/misc/BPD_Arrests.csv")
arrest_table = arrest_table[pandas.notnull(arrest_table["Location 1"])]
arrest_table["lat"], arrest_table["long"] = arrest_table["Location 1"].str.split(",").str
arrest_table["lat"] = arrest_table["lat"].str.replace("(", "").astype(float)
arrest_table["long"] = arrest_table["long"].str.replace(")", "").astype(float)

# Since the number of data points are too large to display on the map, we will just randomly choose sample of them.
arrest_table_sample=arrest_table.sample(n = 100)
arrest_table_sample.head()

map_osm = folium.Map(location=[39.29, -76.61], zoom_start=11)

Now Adding Location Markers Indicating Sex¶

Red indicates Female¶
Darkblue indicates Male¶
In [17]:
feature_group_male = folium.FeatureGroup(name='M')
feature_group_female = folium.FeatureGroup(name='F')
In [18]:
from folium.plugins import MarkerCluster

marker_cluster_male = MarkerCluster()
marker_cluster_female =MarkerCluster()
for index, data in arrest_table_sample.iterrows():
    if(arrest_table_sample.at[index,"sex"]=="M"):
        marker_male = folium.Marker(location=[arrest_table_sample.at[index,"lat"], arrest_table_sample.at[index,"long"]], popup="MALE",icon=folium.Icon(color='darkblue', icon_color='white', icon='male', angle=0, prefix='fa'))
        marker_cluster_male.add_child(marker_male)
    else:
        marker_female = folium.Marker(location=[arrest_table_sample.at[index,"lat"], arrest_table_sample.at[index,"long"]], popup="FEMALE",icon = folium.Icon(color='darkred',icon_color = 'white', icon='female', angle=0,prefix='fa'))
        marker_cluster_female.add_child(marker_female)
In [19]:
feature_group_male.add_child(marker_cluster_male)
feature_group_female.add_child(marker_cluster_female)
map_osm.add_child(feature_group_male)
map_osm.add_child(feature_group_female)
Out[19]:

In this interactive map, I added a blue bubble marker with man icon to indicate crimes that were committed by men, and a red bubble marker with woman icon to indicate crimes that were committed by women. I randomized the sample in attempt to eliminate bias.

Looking at central Baltimore, we can see that most of the crime were committed by men. The ratio of crimes committed by men vs women is roughly about 7:3, by looking at the map. There is no interesting pattern in the relationship of crimes committed and gender, except for the fact that there are more male criminals than female criminals.

Grey indicates the Black Race for criminals¶

for index, data in arrest_table_sample.iterrows():
    if(arrest_table_sample.at[index,"race"]=="B"):
        folium.CircleMarker(location=[arrest_table_sample.at[index,"lat"], arrest_table_sample.at[index,"long"]],radius=5,popup='Black Criminals',color='darkgrey',fill=True,fill_color='darkgrey').add_to(map_osm)
    else:
        folium.CircleMarker(location=[arrest_table_sample.at[index,"lat"], arrest_table_sample.at[index,"long"]],radius=5,popup='Black Criminals',color='purple',fill=True,fill_color='purple').add_to(map_osm)

Out[20]:

In this map, I added color markers to indicate the race of criminals. I use dark grey to indicate Black race, and purple for other races because of the lack of sample. As we can see, majority of the criminals in the Baltimore area are Arican American. But considering the composition of residents in Baltimore, we can see that is the case.

Now Adding Circle Markers indicating Age¶

Lightgreen indicates young offenders with age < 21¶
Blue indicates middle-age offenders with age in [21,40]¶
Darkgreen indicates old offenders with age above 40¶
In [21]:
for index, data in arrest_table_sample.iterrows():
    
    if(arrest_table_sample.at[index,"age"]<21):
        folium.CircleMarker(location=[arrest_table_sample.at[index,"lat"], arrest_table_sample.at[index,"long"]],radius=10,popup='Age<21',color='lightgreen',fill=True,fill_color='lightgreen').add_to(map_osm)    
    elif(arrest_table_sample.at[index,"age"]<40):
        folium.CircleMarker(location=[arrest_table_sample.at[index,"lat"], arrest_table_sample.at[index,"long"]],radius=10,popup='Age<40',color='cornflowerblue',fill=True,fill_color='cornflowerblue').add_to(map_osm)    
    else:
        folium.CircleMarker(location=[arrest_table_sample.at[index,"lat"], arrest_table_sample.at[index,"long"]],radius=10,popup='Age>40',color='darkgreen',fill=True,fill_color='darkgreen').add_to(map_osm)
        
map_osm
Out[21]:

Now in the final step, I added markers to indicate the age of criminals. On this interactive map, I use lightgreen to indicate criminals who are younger than 21. Lightblue markers are used to indicate criminals who are between 21 to 40 of age, and dark green markers are used to indicate criminals who are over 40.

By looking at the map, we can observe that almost half of the criminals are over 40, and the other half are between 21 and 40. The proportion of criminals younger than 21 is small, comparing to the proportions of other two groups. But this might not be the best indicator because people younger than 21 lacks the physicality to commit a crime, and the dark green marker can indicate anyone who is between 40 and 120.
